 the Doctrine of Right, the Critiques, and the political essays but also Kant's lectures and minor writings-the volume's distinguished contributors demonstrate that Kant's philosophy offers compelling positions that continue to inspire the best thinking on politics today.Aside from the editor, the contributors are Michaele Ferguson, Louis-Philippe Hodgson, Ian Hunter, John Christian Laursen, Mika LaVaque-Manty, Onora O'Neill, Thomas W. Pogge, Arthur Ripstein, and Robert S. Taylor.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh1 aEllis, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEllis, Elisabeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFerguson, Michaele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodgson, Louis-Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunter, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaVaque-Manty, Mika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaursen, John Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO'Neill, Onora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPogge, Thomas W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRipstein, Arthur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Robert S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271059860423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780271059860.jpg  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Comple